73
00:09:55,680 --> 00:09:57,400
- Are the police here yet?
- Yes.

74
00:09:58,000 --> 00:09:59,400
So are Mr. Taiga and everyone.

75
00:10:00,240 --> 00:10:03,000
Punlop doesn't know
it's your plan to lure him with money

76
00:10:03,080 --> 00:10:05,520
while Mr. Taiga and everyone
are helping us.

77
00:10:13,720 --> 00:10:15,040
A guy like Punlop

78
00:10:15,120 --> 00:10:17,240
can't be cornered so easily.

79
00:10:17,880 --> 00:10:20,400
We just have to guess correctly
on what he wants the most.

80
00:11:01,280 --> 00:11:02,320
Why can't I transfer it?

81
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:53,000
Dhammatat! Dhammatat.

82
00:11:53,080 --> 00:11:54,040
Dhammatat.

83
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:57,080
Hang in there.

84
00:11:58,160 --> 00:11:59,440
Take a deep breath.

85
00:12:22,160 --> 00:12:24,360
Go ahead. Shoot the vial of virus.

86
00:12:25,400 --> 00:12:26,480
Sure.

87
00:12:26,560 --> 00:12:29,280
Even if I die along with you,
it'll be worth it for me.

88
00:12:29,880 --> 00:12:30,800
Good.

89
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:34,360
Then let the virus
spread all over this place

90
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:36,240
so Taiga and his guys can die too.

91
00:12:36,800 --> 00:12:39,280
And you'd be mistaken
to think I only brought one vial.

92
00:12:40,080 --> 00:12:43,320
You'll never know
where I hid the rest of them.

93
00:12:43,400 --> 00:12:45,960
You piece of shit.

94
00:12:46,640 --> 00:12:48,920
When you're desperate,
all you do is use people's lives.

95
00:12:49,560 --> 00:12:50,720
You never changed.

96
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:53,320
And you never stopped
being stupid like always,

97
00:12:53,400 --> 00:12:54,480
Khanin.

98
00:13:37,880 --> 00:13:39,080
What's up, my lovely niece?

99
00:14:18,680 --> 00:14:19,760
Okay.

100
00:14:21,240 --> 00:14:22,240
What a dream team.

101
00:14:24,240 --> 00:14:26,600
You've got a strong friendship. Good!

102
00:14:27,480 --> 00:14:29,080
You should've died long ago.

103
00:14:30,240 --> 00:14:31,240
Bring out the virus.

104
00:14:32,560 --> 00:14:33,760
Bring it out!

105
00:14:41,160 --> 00:14:43,760
Go ahead! Fine!

106
00:14:45,080 --> 00:14:47,160
Let's die and meet Phumin together.

107
00:14:53,520 --> 00:14:54,400
Look out, Khanin!

108
00:14:58,600 --> 00:14:59,720
Damn you, Punlop!

109
00:15:02,080 --> 00:15:03,080
Let her go.

110
00:15:05,400 --> 00:15:06,640
Now!

111
00:15:13,200 --> 00:15:14,200
Don't!

112
00:15:18,480 --> 00:15:19,440
Rin!

113
00:16:19,440 --> 00:16:20,400
Are you okay, Rin?

114
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:23,560
Please take care of her, Khanin.

115
00:16:26,520 --> 00:16:27,480
Are you good?

116
00:16:40,680 --> 00:16:42,040
I'll kill you!

117
00:16:42,120 --> 00:16:43,800
My parents wanted you to suffer.

118
00:16:43,880 --> 00:16:45,800
I'll never leave you alone.

119
00:16:45,880 --> 00:16:48,000
I'll make sure you live a painful life.

120
00:16:48,600 --> 00:16:49,480
You deserve to die!

121
00:16:49,560 --> 00:16:50,840
You deserve to die!

122
00:16:50,920 --> 00:16:52,000
Why?!

123
00:16:52,960 --> 00:16:56,960
Why do you resent me so much
that you'd hurt our family?

124
00:16:59,720 --> 00:17:01,720
- Mom!
- Go after Naruban!

125
00:17:05,040 --> 00:17:06,240
I never knew

126
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:08,920
that my family hurt you this much.

127
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:12,240
I'm sorry, Giranun.

128
00:17:12,319 --> 00:17:15,240
You're sorry? Well, I don't forgive you!

129
00:17:15,839 --> 00:17:17,079
Give me my life back.

130
00:17:17,160 --> 00:17:18,760
Give me my parents back, then.

131
00:17:18,839 --> 00:17:20,839
I'll kill you! I'll kill you!

132
00:17:20,920 --> 00:17:22,240
- I'll kill you!
- Ma'am,

133
00:17:22,319 --> 00:17:23,240
please calm down.

134
00:17:24,440 --> 00:17:25,280
Let me go!

135
00:17:27,680 --> 00:17:30,240
You deserve to die! Go to hell!

136
00:17:30,320 --> 00:17:32,680
Go! You deserve to die! Go!

137
00:17:32,760 --> 00:17:33,640
Officer,

138
00:17:34,680 --> 00:17:37,880
I was the one who orchestrated
everything. My wife didn't know anything.

139
00:17:38,480 --> 00:17:40,760
Yes! Everything is your fault.

140
00:17:40,840 --> 00:17:43,480
You deserve to die! Go to hell, Naruban!

141
00:17:43,560 --> 00:17:45,040
Go to hell!

142
00:17:45,120 --> 00:17:46,840
You deserve to die! You deserve it!

143
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:56,320
INCOMING CALL - FIRE PHOENIX

144
00:17:57,760 --> 00:17:59,800
If 3C's stocks drop any further,

145
00:18:01,280 --> 00:18:04,800
I hope you know whose life
you'll have to pay with.

146
00:18:53,720 --> 00:18:54,640
Punlop!

147
00:19:13,280 --> 00:19:14,480
Rin.

148
00:19:31,040 --> 00:19:32,160
Shoot me, Rin.

149
00:19:32,720 --> 00:19:34,360
If you want to see
your loved one die, do it!

150
00:19:40,360 --> 00:19:41,760
Heal all your pain.

151
00:19:42,840 --> 00:19:44,040
Start your life over, Rin.

152
00:19:54,200 --> 00:19:55,280
Taiga!

153
00:19:57,160 --> 00:20:00,040
Taiga, Taiga!

154
00:20:00,640 --> 00:20:01,600
Taiga!

155
00:20:03,760 --> 00:20:04,880
Taiga!

156
00:20:06,080 --> 00:20:07,360
Taiga!

157
00:20:11,880 --> 00:20:12,920
Taiga!

158
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:42,400
Excuse me.

159
00:20:50,080 --> 00:20:53,040
For all the evidence I've gathered
against Fire Phoenix,

160
00:20:54,440 --> 00:20:56,360
every case, every order,

161
00:20:58,200 --> 00:21:00,640
every case where Damon
ordered a hit on someone,

162
00:21:02,520 --> 00:21:05,000
the networks, as well
as the bribe money I paid

163
00:21:05,080 --> 00:21:08,680
to the police,
prosecutors, and politicians,

164
00:21:10,840 --> 00:21:12,880
I'm happy to testify about everything.

165
00:21:13,680 --> 00:21:15,560
Feel free to take legal action against me.

166
00:21:34,080 --> 00:21:35,560
Take good care of 3C, kids.

167
00:21:37,720 --> 00:21:39,480
Work together, okay?

168
00:21:41,480 --> 00:21:43,320
- You hear me?
- Yes, Dad.

169
00:21:43,960 --> 00:21:44,880
Yes.

170
00:21:59,840 --> 00:22:01,680
Come visit me in jail sometime.

171
00:22:04,080 --> 00:22:05,880
I'll go and talk to you often.

172
00:22:07,120 --> 00:22:08,120
I'm sorry, Rin.

173
00:22:10,120 --> 00:22:12,080
Sorry for being a coward

174
00:22:12,160 --> 00:22:15,800
and being so selfish
that you had to lose so much.

175
00:22:17,400 --> 00:22:20,000
It's okay. I could bear it.

176
00:22:22,360 --> 00:22:24,320
Thank you, Mr. Naruban.

177
00:22:28,440 --> 00:22:29,360
Right this way.

178
00:22:33,240 --> 00:22:34,200
Excuse me.

179
00:22:37,320 --> 00:22:38,320
This way, please.

180
00:22:43,640 --> 00:22:44,800
Dad!

181
00:23:04,840 --> 00:23:07,200
Are you really going
to stay alone like this?

182
00:23:07,800 --> 00:23:09,600
Why don't you go see Mr. Taiga?

183
00:23:12,520 --> 00:23:13,800
He hasn't come home yet.

184
00:23:15,120 --> 00:23:17,480
He's been gone
since he and Punlop fell into the river.

185
00:23:20,320 --> 00:23:21,800
I don't know where he went.

186
00:23:23,520 --> 00:23:25,000
Who knows how he is

187
00:23:26,960 --> 00:23:28,280
or if he even made it.

188
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:32,160
No one can give me an answer.

189
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:36,880
He didn't reach anyone

190
00:23:38,720 --> 00:23:40,160
or contact anyone at all.

191
00:23:42,360 --> 00:23:44,280
I don't know where to find him.

192
00:23:57,000 --> 00:23:59,400
I think you should go find him

193
00:24:00,640 --> 00:24:03,320
where you and him were happy together.

194
00:24:32,280 --> 00:24:33,680
<i>Whenever I miss you,</i>

195
00:24:34,400 --> 00:24:38,360
<i>I always try to think of the reason</i>
<i>why you make me smile,</i>

196
00:24:38,440 --> 00:24:39,520
<i>get me excited,</i>

197
00:24:40,240 --> 00:24:42,080
<i>or want to stare at you for a long time.</i>

198
00:24:48,640 --> 00:24:50,640
<i>I wish memories had a scent</i>

199
00:24:51,560 --> 00:24:53,520
<i>that fills the air around me every day.</i>

200
00:24:54,080 --> 00:24:56,240
<i>Every time we smell something nice,</i>

201
00:24:56,800 --> 00:24:59,040
<i>we'll think of the smell of the wind,</i>

202
00:24:59,120 --> 00:25:01,160
<i>sunlight, flowers,</i>

203
00:25:02,040 --> 00:25:03,880
<i>and the happiness around you.</i>

204
00:26:29,880 --> 00:26:32,040
<i>I want a beautiful phoenix such as you</i>

205
00:26:32,800 --> 00:26:35,440
<i>to be reborn from the ashes of pain.</i>

206
00:26:37,200 --> 00:26:39,200
<i>Please live the rest of your life happily,</i>

207
00:26:40,000 --> 00:26:41,000
<i>Rin.</i>

208
00:28:21,480 --> 00:28:24,680
You silly bear!
Get up before my suitcase breaks!

209
00:28:27,560 --> 00:28:29,920
Be nice to the one
who's taking you to the airport.

210
00:28:31,640 --> 00:28:32,800
Where's your car then?

211
00:28:33,720 --> 00:28:35,880
We'll call a cab around here.

212
00:28:39,120 --> 00:28:42,480
What now? Are you leaving for good?

213
00:28:44,800 --> 00:28:46,280
Won't you miss anything here?

214
00:28:48,640 --> 00:28:49,560
No.

215
00:28:53,320 --> 00:28:56,720
So, if I go to your house, madam,

216
00:28:58,000 --> 00:29:00,000
can you treat me to a fancy meal?

217
00:29:01,520 --> 00:29:03,320
Hurry and join me there.
I'll take you on a trip.

218
00:29:04,440 --> 00:29:06,520
You're so rich, aren't you?

219
00:29:11,880 --> 00:29:12,920
Did you hear about him?

220
00:29:13,760 --> 00:29:14,680
Who?

221
00:29:16,320 --> 00:29:17,600
You mean Taiga?

222
00:29:21,840 --> 00:29:23,960
I don't need to know
about some guy anymore.

223
00:29:32,040 --> 00:29:32,880
"Some guy," huh?

224
00:29:35,600 --> 00:29:36,560
Yeah.

225
00:29:37,520 --> 00:29:38,640
What's past is past.

226
00:29:39,680 --> 00:29:41,680
An ex is just an ex.

227
00:29:46,040 --> 00:29:47,240
Move already.

228
00:29:58,160 --> 00:29:59,200
Well,

229
00:30:00,080 --> 00:30:01,080
so…

230
00:30:02,080 --> 00:30:03,440
would you like someone new?

231
00:30:07,600 --> 00:30:08,520
Are you flirting with me?

232
00:30:10,680 --> 00:30:12,960
Why would I? With a girl like you, madam,

233
00:30:13,040 --> 00:30:15,200
you'll come as soon as I beckon.

234
00:30:16,560 --> 00:30:18,080
You silly bear. Stupid bear.

235
00:30:18,160 --> 00:30:20,880
You're the one who'll come
as soon as I beckon.

236
00:30:28,440 --> 00:30:31,200
Are you taking me there?
If you are, then follow me.

237
00:30:31,800 --> 00:30:33,600
Come on, hurry.

238
00:30:39,720 --> 00:30:40,560
Fine.

239
00:30:55,520 --> 00:30:58,000
So you've moved in for good?

240
00:30:59,160 --> 00:31:00,480
No, I haven't!

241
00:31:00,560 --> 00:31:03,520
The owner of the house said
I could do whatever I want,

242
00:31:03,600 --> 00:31:05,760
so I turned it into a delivery shop.

243
00:31:06,760 --> 00:31:09,320
But don't you want
to be a designer anymore?

244
00:31:10,720 --> 00:31:13,680
Of course I do.
I have to be one, no matter what.

245
00:31:14,600 --> 00:31:16,880
But I'm still not done practicing.

246
00:31:17,480 --> 00:31:20,480
Once I launch my first collection,
don't forget to be my customer.

247
00:31:20,560 --> 00:31:21,760
Of course.

248
00:31:26,040 --> 00:31:27,280
- Aru,
- Hm?

249
00:31:28,120 --> 00:31:29,960
Can I partner with you?

250
00:31:34,360 --> 00:31:37,320
You mean my desserts shop
or my clothes shop?

251
00:31:37,920 --> 00:31:39,080
Both of those.

252
00:31:43,920 --> 00:31:48,360
It'll take a while to get rich, Sun.
It's unlike when you trade coins.

253
00:31:49,560 --> 00:31:51,720
It's good to enjoy a slow life sometimes.

254
00:31:58,880 --> 00:32:01,680
Walking slowly, but with someone

255
00:32:01,760 --> 00:32:03,240
makes it not so lonely.

256
00:32:07,040 --> 00:32:10,080
In my life, I'm not afraid of loneliness.

257
00:32:12,520 --> 00:32:14,800
It teaches me to have patience

258
00:32:14,880 --> 00:32:17,200
and to wait for success.

259
00:32:19,680 --> 00:32:21,120
Have you ever felt lonely?

260
00:32:23,560 --> 00:32:24,560
Of course.

261
00:32:26,520 --> 00:32:27,880
So you can be patient, right?

262
00:32:30,360 --> 00:32:33,240
I can. I can wait.

263
00:32:34,760 --> 00:32:36,840
From now on, allow me to wait for you too.

264
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:43,840
Great. I'll give my all to my work.

265
00:32:45,120 --> 00:32:46,640
These desserts

266
00:32:46,720 --> 00:32:49,320
will be my future,
which I'll shape with my own hands.

267
00:32:53,960 --> 00:32:54,960
Let me help you.

268
00:33:02,080 --> 00:33:04,040
- Sure.
- Eight per box, right?

269
00:33:08,960 --> 00:33:09,960
Three.

270
00:33:11,680 --> 00:33:13,160
- Four.
- Careful. Don't drop it.

271
00:33:26,560 --> 00:33:28,240
What will you do with 3C now?

272
00:33:30,480 --> 00:33:33,440
I'll just have to move forward.
3C is the future.

273
00:33:35,080 --> 00:33:36,320
What about you, Te?

274
00:33:37,560 --> 00:33:38,520
It's your call.

275
00:33:41,640 --> 00:33:45,400
How are things between you and Taiga?

276
00:33:47,360 --> 00:33:48,640
It's over, Te.

277
00:33:49,880 --> 00:33:51,280
He's just a guy.

278
00:33:52,360 --> 00:33:54,400
He'll no longer influence my life.

279
00:33:56,600 --> 00:33:58,520
I can stand on my own two feet.

280
00:34:08,400 --> 00:34:09,639
It's this place

281
00:34:10,360 --> 00:34:12,239
that I'll devote my life to.

282
00:34:13,760 --> 00:34:16,280
We'll make sure 3C thrives again, Te.

283
00:34:20,199 --> 00:34:23,440
Once I'm rich,
I'll have plenty of guys chasing me.

284
00:34:25,239 --> 00:34:27,360
I should be the one to choose,

285
00:34:28,840 --> 00:34:31,400
not cry my eyes out and beg.

286
00:34:33,000 --> 00:34:34,159
That's nonsense.

287
00:34:44,840 --> 00:34:46,440
You've proven to me

288
00:34:47,480 --> 00:34:51,760
that you're strong enough
to bring 3C to reach your goal.

289
00:34:54,679 --> 00:34:57,600
Go on, then. Do your best.

290
00:34:57,680 --> 00:34:58,680
Give it your all.

291
00:34:59,960 --> 00:35:02,080
I'll always be right by your side.

292
00:35:30,680 --> 00:35:31,600
Ryu's here.

293
00:35:38,320 --> 00:35:39,520
You said you needed some time,

294
00:35:40,320 --> 00:35:41,360
but still, you came.

295
00:35:42,160 --> 00:35:43,400
I'm glad.

296
00:35:43,480 --> 00:35:45,440
I'm here to ask for the truth
about my family.

297
00:35:46,520 --> 00:35:47,960
Your mom must've told you a few things.

298
00:35:48,760 --> 00:35:50,360
That's why you came.

299
00:35:50,960 --> 00:35:53,440
I want to hear it from you, Khanin.

300
00:36:10,640 --> 00:36:14,280
Your mother, Sabaiprae,
once sent me this photo.

301
00:36:15,760 --> 00:36:19,400
She said she's very happy.

302
00:36:20,240 --> 00:36:21,720
So I congratulated her.

303
00:36:22,520 --> 00:36:23,920
But I never thought that one day

304
00:36:24,000 --> 00:36:26,160
you three would get to see
this picture together.

305
00:36:30,280 --> 00:36:31,160
Prae,

306
00:36:32,200 --> 00:36:33,800
your three sons,

307
00:36:35,280 --> 00:36:36,640
Prab,

308
00:36:37,240 --> 00:36:38,120
Pun,

309
00:36:39,640 --> 00:36:41,240
I took care of them

310
00:36:42,640 --> 00:36:44,840
as best I could.

311
00:37:10,800 --> 00:37:12,360
Fire Phoenix killed our parents.

312
00:37:13,600 --> 00:37:15,400
About Fire Phoenix, I handled it already.

313
00:37:15,480 --> 00:37:17,520
But you both need to be careful.

314
00:37:17,600 --> 00:37:20,040
Fire Phoenix has their guys
all over the world.

315
00:37:21,360 --> 00:37:22,280
Got it, Ryu?

316
00:37:25,080 --> 00:37:26,200
You too.

317
00:37:32,000 --> 00:37:33,520
Please be careful,

318
00:37:34,240 --> 00:37:36,000
in case they're getting back at you.

319
00:37:45,680 --> 00:37:46,800
I still haven't thanked you

320
00:37:48,280 --> 00:37:49,320
for saving me from the bomb.

321
00:37:53,280 --> 00:37:54,600
I survived because of you two.

322
00:37:56,680 --> 00:37:58,120
I really appreciate it.

323
00:38:03,680 --> 00:38:05,360
It's what brothers should do.

324
00:38:10,560 --> 00:38:12,040
I still have to work in Hong Kong,

325
00:38:14,600 --> 00:38:16,480
but I'll probably
visit Thailand more often.

326
00:38:21,160 --> 00:38:22,400
This is your home country.

327
00:38:24,960 --> 00:38:26,440
Whenever you want to come back,

328
00:38:27,160 --> 00:38:29,320
your family's always ready to welcome you.

329
00:38:58,440 --> 00:39:00,280
Right now, I wish you were here the most,

330
00:39:01,640 --> 00:39:03,800
so you could see
that Fire Phoenix was destroyed.

331
00:39:07,840 --> 00:39:09,360
I miss you, Dad.

332
00:39:44,920 --> 00:39:46,960
It's all over now, brother.

333
00:39:50,000 --> 00:39:51,600
Your sacrifice…

334
00:39:54,080 --> 00:39:55,560
means everything.

335
00:40:05,600 --> 00:40:07,200
Have you found Taiga?

336
00:40:14,480 --> 00:40:15,720
You regret it, don't you?

337
00:40:18,680 --> 00:40:20,840
Your moments of happiness with Taiga

338
00:40:22,120 --> 00:40:23,760
were so fleeting.

339
00:40:25,960 --> 00:40:27,360
But I never forgot.

340
00:40:28,400 --> 00:40:29,800
If you get one more chance,

341
00:40:30,560 --> 00:40:32,720
will you choose your heart this time,

342
00:40:33,320 --> 00:40:34,680
or will you throw it away again?

343
00:40:49,040 --> 00:40:51,320
Whenever your heart is ready…

344
00:40:53,560 --> 00:40:55,280
open this envelope.

345
00:42:42,880 --> 00:42:43,960
I fell into the river,

346
00:42:46,120 --> 00:42:47,920
and I was struggling
like when I was little.

347
00:42:50,920 --> 00:42:53,600
But I told myself I wouldn't die.

348
00:42:54,960 --> 00:42:58,400
The water carried me far away.
Luckily, the locals saved me.

349
00:43:01,080 --> 00:43:02,560
It took a while until I recovered.

350
00:43:24,440 --> 00:43:26,920
I thought I could be alone like I used to.

351
00:43:28,960 --> 00:43:30,600
I've been lonely since I was little.

352
00:43:31,800 --> 00:43:34,760
Nobody's touch could ever fill
the void inside my heart.

353
00:44:35,800 --> 00:44:37,160
I miss this scent.

354
00:44:41,800 --> 00:44:43,080
My happiness.

355
00:44:50,200 --> 00:44:51,560
So you want to be alone?

356
00:44:55,080 --> 00:44:56,600
I can't be alone anymore.

357
00:45:57,360 --> 00:46:03,960
THE END

358
00:46:32,800 --> 00:46:34,360
Subtitle translation by:
Ramil Natnitiwitaya
